## Topic 2: Addition & Subtraction within 100

### History & the Idea

Once you have place value, you can line up the ones, tens, and hundreds and add or subtract column by column. If the ones add up to more than 9, you *carry* a ten to the tens place. If you need to subtract more ones than you have, you *borrow* a ten from the tens place and turn it into 10 ones. These algorithms—carry and borrow—were taught in European schools by the 1200s and are still the standard method today.

### What We'll Cover

We'll add and subtract two-digit numbers, watching carries and borrows happen, and plot the results on a number line.

---

### Example 6: Simple Addition within 100

<!-- BUILD: Add 23 + 45, print the sum, plot both addends and the sum on a number line. -->

```scheme
(define a 23)
(define b 45)
(define sum (+ a b))

(display a)
(display \" + \")
(display b)
(display \" = \")
(display sum)
(newline)

(plot/scatter (list (list a 0) (list b 0) (list sum 1))
              '((title \"23 + 45 = 68 on the Number Line\")
                (x-label \"value\")
                (y-label \"\")
                (width 600)
                (height 120)))
```

[VISUAL: A number line from 0 to 100 with points at 23, 45, and 68 (the sum marked at a higher y-level to stand out).]

---

### Example 7: Addition with a Carry

<!-- BUILD: Add 47 + 38, which carries a ten; print the breakdown, plot the sum. -->

```scheme
(define a 47)
(define b 38)
(define sum (+ a b))

(display a)
(display \" + \")
(display b)
(display \" = \")
(display sum)
(display \" (ones: 7+8=15, write 5 carry 1; tens: 4+3+1=8)\")
(newline)

(plot/scatter (list (list a 0) (list b 0) (list sum 1))
              '((title \"47 + 38 = 85 (with carry)\")
                (x-label \"value\")
                (y-label \"\")
                (width 600)
                (height 120)))
```

[VISUAL: Number line with 47, 38, and 85 marked; a note or label showing the carry step.]

---

### Example 8: Subtraction without Borrowing

<!-- BUILD: Subtract 68 - 23, print the difference, plot. -->

```scheme
(define a 68)
(define b 23)
(define diff (- a b))

(display a)
(display \" - \")
(display b)
(display \" = \")
(display diff)
(newline)

(plot/scatter (list (list a 1) (list b 0) (list diff 0))
              '((title \"68 - 23 = 45\")
                (x-label \"value\")
                (y-label \"\")
                (width 600)
                (height 120)))
```

[VISUAL: Number line showing 68, 23, and 45, with 68 and 45 highlighted to show the minuend and difference.]

---

### Example 9: Subtraction with Borrowing

<!-- BUILD: Subtract 52 - 27, which requires borrowing a ten; print the breakdown, plot. -->

```scheme
(define a 52)
(define b 27)
(define diff (- a b))

(display a)
(display \" - \")
(display b)
(display \" = \")
(display diff)
(display \" (ones: can't do 2-7, borrow 1 ten: 12-7=5; tens: 4-2=2)\")
(newline)

(plot/scatter (list (list a 1) (list b 0) (list diff 0))
              '((title \"52 - 27 = 25 (with borrow)\")
                (x-label \"value\")
                (y-label \"\")
                (width 600)
                (height 120)))
```

[VISUAL: Number line with 52, 27, and 25 marked; annotation showing the borrow step.]

