### Example 10: Adding Three Numbers

<!-- BUILD: Add 12 + 23 + 34, print the running totals, plot all three addends and the final sum. -->

```scheme
(define a 12)
(define b 23)
(define c 34)
(define sum1 (+ a b))
(define sum2 (+ sum1 c))

(display a)
(display \" + \")
(display b)
(display \" = \")
(display sum1)
(newline)
(display sum1)
(display \" + \")
(display c)
(display \" = \")
(display sum2)
(newline)

(plot/scatter (list (list a 0) (list b 0) (list c 0) (list sum2 1))
              '((title \"12 + 23 + 34 = 69\")
                (x-label \"value\")
                (y-label \"\")
                (width 600)
                (height 120)))
```

[VISUAL: Number line with four points: 12, 23, 34 at y=0, and the sum 69 at y=1.]

