## Topic 3: Addition & Subtraction within 1000

### History & the Idea

The same carry-and-borrow algorithm scales to any number of digits. By the Renaissance, merchants used it to total invoices with hundreds of line items. The only new idea is keeping track of the hundreds place alongside tens and ones.

### What We'll Cover

We'll add and subtract three-digit numbers, watching carries ripple through multiple places, and plot the results.

---

### Example 11: Adding Two Three-Digit Numbers

<!-- BUILD: Add 234 + 567, print the sum, plot on a number line to 1000. -->

```scheme
(define a 234)
(define b 567)
(define sum (+ a b))

(display a)
(display \" + \")
(display b)
(display \" = \")
(display sum)
(newline)

(plot/scatter (list (list a 0) (list b 0) (list sum 1))
              '((title \"234 + 567 = 801\")
                (x-label \"value\")
                (y-label \"\")
                (width 800)
                (height 120)))
```

[VISUAL: Number line from 0 to 1000 with points at 234, 567, and 801.]

---

