### Example 28: Counting an Array by Rows (Using a Loop)

<!-- BUILD: Write a function that takes rows and cols, returns the total by adding cols 'rows' times. -->

```scheme
(define (count-array-by-rows rows cols)
  (let loop ((r 0) (total 0))
    (if (>= r rows)
        total
        (loop (+ r 1) (+ total cols)))))

(define r 5)
(define c 4)
(define total (count-array-by-rows r c))

(display \"A \")
(display r)
(display \"×\")
(display c)
(display \" array has \")
(display total)
(display \" dots (counted by rows)\")
(newline)
```

[VISUAL: Printed output \"A 5×4 array has 20 dots (counted by rows)\".]

