### Example 29: Counting an Array by Columns

<!-- BUILD: Same idea, but add 'rows' a total of 'cols' times. -->

```scheme
(define (count-array-by-cols rows cols)
  (let loop ((c 0) (total 0))
    (if (>= c cols)
        total
        (loop (+ c 1) (+ total rows)))))

(define r 5)
(define c 4)
(define total (count-array-by-cols r c))

(display \"A \")
(display r)
(display \"×\")
(display c)
(display \" array has \")
(display total)
(display \" dots (counted by columns)\")
(newline)
```

[VISUAL: Printed output \"A 5×4 array has 20 dots (counted by columns)\".]

