### Example 30: Drawing a Larger Array (6×5)

<!-- BUILD: Draw 6 rows of 5 dots each, count it both ways, plot. -->

```scheme
(define rows 6)
(define cols 5)

(define (count-by-rows r c)
  (let loop ((i 0) (total 0))
    (if (>= i r) total (loop (+ i 1) (+ total c)))))

(define (count-by-cols r c)
  (let loop ((i 0) (total 0))
    (if (>= i c) total (loop (+ i 1) (+ total r)))))

(define total-rows (count-by-rows rows cols))
(define total-cols (count-by-cols rows cols))

(display \"By rows: \")
(display total-rows)
(display \"; by columns: \")
(display total-cols)
(newline)

(define (make-grid r c)
  (let loop-r ((row 0) (acc '()))
    (if (>= row r)
        acc
        (let loop-c ((col 0) (acc2 acc))
          (if (>= col c)
              (loop-r (+ row 1) acc2)
              (loop-c (+ col 1) (cons (list (* col 30) (* row 30)) acc2)))))))

(define points (make-grid rows cols))
(plot/scatter points
              '((title \"6×5 Array (30 dots)\")
                (x-label \"column\")
                (y-label \"row\")
                (width 200)
                (height 220)))
```

[VISUAL: A 6×5 grid of dots, evenly spaced; printed output \"By rows: 30; by columns: 30\".]

