### Example 32: Summing the Row Counts to Get the Total

<!-- BUILD: For a 5×3 array, print each row's count (3, 3, 3, 3, 3), then sum them. -->

```scheme
(define rows 5)
(define cols 3)

(define (sum-rows r c)
  (let loop ((i 0) (acc '()))
    (if (>= i r)
        (reverse acc)
        (loop (+ i 1) (cons c acc)))))

(define row-counts (sum-rows rows cols))
(display \"Row counts: \")
(display row-counts)
(newline)

(define total (apply + row-counts))
(display \"Total: \")
(display total)
(newline)
```

[VISUAL: Printed output \"Row counts: (3 3 3 3 3)\" and \"Total: 15\".]

