### Example 33: An Array with Different Row Sizes (Irregular)

<!-- BUILD: Draw a \"ragged\" array where row 0 has 2 dots, row 1 has 3 dots, row 2 has 4 dots; count the total. -->

```scheme
(define row-sizes (list 2 3 4))

(display \"Row sizes: \")
(display row-sizes)
(newline)

(define total (apply + row-sizes))
(display \"Total dots: \")
(display total)
(newline)

;; Render each row at a different y, with the right number of dots
(define (make-ragged-grid sizes)
  (let loop-r ((r 0) (sizes-left sizes) (acc '()))
    (if (null? sizes-left)
        acc
        (let ((cols (car sizes-left)))
          (let loop-c ((c 0) (acc2 acc))
            (if (>= c cols)
                (loop-r (+ r 1) (cdr sizes-left) acc2)
                (loop-c (+ c 1) (cons (list (* c 25) (* r 25)) acc2))))))))

(define points (make-ragged-grid row-sizes))
(plot/scatter points
              '((title \"Ragged Array: 2, 3, 4 dots per row\")
                (x-label \"column\")
                (y-label \"row\")
                (width 150)
                (height 100)))
```

[VISUAL: Three rows of dots: top row has 2, middle row has 3, bottom row has 4; printed output \"Row sizes: (2 3 4)\" and \"Total dots: 9\".]

