## Summit Artifact: A 5×4 Dot Array Counted by Rows

<!-- BUILD: This is the chapter's capstone program. Draw a 5×4 array on the canvas, print each row's count, sum them, and display the total. The plot should be clear and labeled. -->

```scheme
;;; Summit Artifact: A 5×4 Dot Array Counted by Rows
;;; We draw 5 rows of 4 dots each, print the count for each row,
;;; and sum them to get the total of 20 dots.

(define rows 5)
(define cols 4)

(display \"=== 5×4 Dot Array ===\")
(newline)

;; Print each row's count
(let loop ((r 0))
  (if (< r rows)
      (begin
        (display \"Row \")
        (display r)
        (display \": \")
        (display cols)
        (display \" dots\")
        (newline)
        (loop (+ r 1)))))

;; Sum the rows
(define total (let loop ((r 0) (acc 0))
                (if (>= r rows)
                    acc
                    (loop (+ r 1) (+ acc cols)))))

(display \"Total (by repeated addition): \")
(display cols)
(display \" + \")
(display cols)
(display \" + \")
(display cols)
(display \" + \")
(display cols)
(display \" + \")
(display cols)
(display \" = \")
(display total)
(newline)

;; Draw the array on the canvas
(define (make-grid r c)
  (let loop-r ((row 0) (acc '()))
    (if (>= row r)
        acc
        (let loop-c ((col 0) (acc2 acc))
          (if (>= col c)
              (loop-r (+ row 1) acc2)
              (loop-c (+ col 1) (cons (list (* col 30) (* row 30)) acc2)))))))

(define points (make-grid rows cols))
(plot/scatter points
              '((title \"Summit: 5×4 Array (20 dots)\")
                (x-label \"column (4 across)\")
                (y-label \"row (5 down)\")
                (width 180)
                (height 200)))

(display \"=== Array rendered on the canvas ===\")
(newline)
```

[VISUAL: A clear 5×4 grid of dots, evenly spaced at 30-pixel intervals, with labels showing 4 columns and 5 rows. Printed output lists each row's count (\"Row 0: 4 dots\", ..., \"Row 4: 4 dots\"), the repeated addition \"4 + 4 + 4 + 4 + 4 = 20\", and a final confirmation that the array is rendered.]

